{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_011RczyQjodV1achj3gNxK3V","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — the operator already has RBAC to manage `prometheusrules`. Now I have everything needed. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Key metrics identified\n\nFrom `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go`:\n- **`mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total`** — counter of failed image inspections\n- **`mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total`** — counter of total pods processed by the controller\n\nThe failure rate is: `rate(failed) / rate(processed)`.\n\n### 1. New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-alert.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/created-by: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: image-inspection-failure-rate\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[5m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[5m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            message: >-\n              The multiarch-tuning-operator image inspection failure rate has exceeded\n              5% over the last 5 minutes. Current value is {{ $value | humanizePercentage }}.\n              This may indicate registry connectivity issues, authentication failures,\n              or misconfigured image references.\n```\n\n### 2. New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n  - prometheus-alert.yaml\n```\n\n### 3. Modify: `config/default/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd `- ../monitoring` to the `resources` list so the PrometheusRule gets deployed alongside the operator. Change the resources section from:\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n```\n\nto:\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\n### 4. Modify: `config/prometheus/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd the monitoring resources here as well, so they're included when the prometheus kustomization overlay is used independently:\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- monitor.yaml\n- ../monitoring/prometheus-alert.yaml\n```\n\n---\n\n## Commands to run\n\nNo special make targets are needed. To verify the YAML is valid kustomize output:\n\n```bash\n# Verify kustomize builds cleanly with the new resources\ncd config/default && kustomize build .\n```\n\n---\n\n## Design decisions\n\n- **`rate(...[5m]) > 0.05` with `for: 5m`**: The `rate()` uses a 5-minute window to smooth out transient spikes. The `for: 5m` clause means the condition must persist for 5 minutes before the alert fires, preventing one-off blips from paging.\n- **5% threshold (0.05)**: A standard SLO threshold — more than 1-in-20 inspections failing is a systemic problem worth alerting on.\n- **`severity: critical`**: Image inspection failures block pod scheduling (pods stay gated), so this is a production-impacting condition.\n- **Namespace `system`**: Matches the convention used by the existing `ServiceMonitor` in `config/prometheus/monitor.yaml` — kustomize's `namespace` transformer in `config/default/kustomization.yaml` will replace `system` with `openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator`.\n- **Both counters come from the same controller metrics package**, so they are always co-registered and scraped from the same `/metrics` endpoint."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":172,"cache_read_input_tokens":41871,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":172,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27e202c6-d2fe-47e8-bfee-e03270c11742","uuid":"49b2b2ec-3088-4f20-bf83-0035d5eb29e3","timestamp":"2026-07-16T13:20:23.321Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011Cd5oc8zFDAmqQhf53DWhE"}
